<TITLE> DCC commissioner Chowdhury Alam gets 13 years </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 26 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court Thursday sentenced Dhaka City Corporation ward commissioner Chowdhury Alam to 13 years for acquiring assets beyond his known income and concealing wealth related information. Judge Shahed Noor Uddin of Special Judge's Court-3 also fined Alam Tk 1 crore or another year in prison on non-payment of the sum. amount The court also sentenced Chowdhury Alam's son Abu Sayeed Chowdhury, and brothers Rahmat Ali Labu and Khorshed Alam Mintu, three years' imprisonment each and Tk 5 lakh fines or another six months behind bars, for abetting the ward commissioner crimes. Alam's wife Hasina Chowdhury, daughters Mahmuda Aktar Monika and Mahfuza Aktar Mukta, and son-in-law Md Selim Mia, were acquitted as charges against them could not be substantiated. The court also ordered confiscation of Alam's illegally acquired assets totaling Tk 4.98 crore. All the accused excepting Chowdhury Alam are fugitive. The Anticorruption Commission filed the case on June 13, 2007, with Khilgaon Police Station. bdnews24.c
